title: What TV channel for Oregon Ducks football at Washington Huskies? Start time, how to watch live stream
text:
Will the streak continue? That is the question as the Oregon Ducks travel to Seattle for a Saturday night rivalry game against the Washington Huskies, a team the Ducks have beaten 11 times in a row.
If the Ducks lose this game, not only will the streak be history, but Oregon will fall to 3-4 for the first time since 1996.
Here's how to watch and follow the game:
What: Oregon Ducks (3-3, 1-2 Pac-12) at Washington Huskies (3-2, 1-1)
When: 7:30 p.m. PDT Saturday (kickoff at 7:36)
Where: Husky Stadium, Seattle. Capacity: 70,138.
TV channel: ESPN2 (Comcast 36/736, CenturyLink 606/1606 in Portland area; DirecTV 209; Dish 143)
Commentators: Mike Patrick (play-by-play), Ed Cunningham (analyst), Jerry Punch (sideline)
Radio: KXTG (750 AM, 102.9 FM), KUGN-AM (590); Sirius 136; XM 201
Live stream: Cable, satellite and internet customers who subscribe to ESPN can stream the game at ESPN3.com or via the Watch ESPN app .
Live chat: Check out our live game chat at oregonlive.com/ducks for updates throughout the game.
Latest line: Washington by 2Â½
Forecast at kickoff: Rain, temperatures in the 50s.
Series history: The Huskies lead the all-time series 58-44-5, but the Ducks have won the past 11 meetings. Washington leads 33-25-4 in Seattle.
